author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Amber Liu. The first time I ever saw you, it was through my older sister who was, and still is, absolutely obsessed with FX. I have been a K-Pop fan for about a decade now, but at this time, at least 5 years ago, I wasn’t acquainted with many groups. I saw the absolute glow in my sister’s eyes as she showed me endless FX music videos and talked about each member with such love and inspiration woven into each of her words. Since then, I have been a huge supporter and fan of FX, and I have grown alongside you during your most difficult and triumphant times. I know that you have been through a lot, and even saying that doesn’t even come to close to what you must have been feeling for the past several years. I know you have been in the business and making music for a very long time now, and I know you have experienced extreme tragedy as well as glorifying victories. I have never seen someone respond to any obstacles in the mature and hopeful manner that you have. That, as I’ve gotten to know more about you over the years, might be what I appreciated the most about you. I am so aware why so many people, including my sister who introduced me to you, are so inspired by you and desperate to follow in your footsteps. Amidst all of the pain you have felt, sacrifice you have made, and challenges you have faced, you continue to make barrier-breaking music and share your voice with the world through that music. Your response to the problems in the world is so wholesome, genuine and confident; and you have taught many around the world how to effectively recover from any pain they may have felt. It can be understood that you have gone through what many have not, and yet you have not given up on living out your dreams and encouraging others to follow in your footsteps. What has always stood out to me is that you have always been confident, and done what has been best for you, rather than listen to others. You always came off as so comfortable in your own skin, and that makes you such an iconic performer and musician. Your powerful and bold rapping, combined with your soulful, smooth, and energetic voice makes you an incredibly compassionate performer who is so connected to her audience and music on stage. You are an unbelievably beautiful dancer and have such a demanding stage presence that has been such a privilege for me to watch over these years. I know that your fans love you in a way that’s stronger than anybody else ever could. You have given them a reason not to give up trying when the worst happens to them, and there is no higher form of inspiration than that. I am proud to be one of these fans, and I know my sister is as well. Similarly, your members love you and have such an unbreakable bond with you that I have seen firsthand without even knowing any of you personally. I know that you have all relied on each other in such a way that most people can’t say they know or understood, and I can’t even speak on how unique your relationship is with one another. I can’t even thank you enough for coming into my life and showing me confidence, strength, and reliance on my passion, friends, and family in the darkest times in my life. You are an inspiration like no other, and I know all of the fans, and even those outside of them can recognize as such a once-in-a-lifetime authentic musician. On behalf of your friends, fans, members, and most importantly, your loving and adoring family, I wish you the most blessed birthday ever Amber. I hope nothing but love surrounds you and those close to you always and forever. Please stay safe, and I pray that you continue to live your life in such bliss as you do now and have always tried to. I absolutely love you so, so much, and Happy Birthday! I hope you have as much fun as you possibly can! We adore you so much and never give up on your once-in-a-lifetime artistry. Be safe, and praying for the happiness and health of you and your loved ones always.

author: @nachochip1778
text: 너무 좋아서 입꼬리랑 광대 승천함 ㅋㅋㅋㅋㅋㅋㅋ 언닝 넘 좋아 예전에도 생각했지만 아이돌치고 자유로워보여서 더 좋아.. 언니 항상 행복했음 좋겠다. 이 곡 나왔을 땐 어렸고 함수 나왔을 때 남자냐 여자냐 말 많았는데 지금은 언니가 유별난 게 아니라 오히려 사람다운 상태로 살았던 걸 알게됐어. 어릴 때도 태연이랑 언니랑 번갈아나오는데 의상은 극과 극이라 왜 다르지? 궁금했던 게 생각나는데 그땐 그정도 의문만 가졌지 그 이상을 생각할 순 없었어. 머리 짧고 활동성 좋은 옷 입는다고 한국에선 남자 외국에선 톰보이라고 말하는 거 참 지긋지긋하다. 보는 나도 그런데 함수활동하면서 그런 시비는 끝도없이 들었을 게 뻔해서 마음이 아프네. 많은 아이돌이나 일반인 여자들이 언니같이 활동성 좋은 옷을 입고 메이크업 압박도 개인적으로나 사회적으로나 줄어들면 좋겠어. 나도 중학생 때 머리 조금 짧게 잘랐었는데 흔히 말하는 여성숏컷이었음에도 불구하고 남자냐는 말 많이 들었거든. 이상한 애 보는 듯한 눈빛이 싫어서 결국 머리 길렀었는데... 언니가 끝까지 남들의 강요나 꼽주는거에 굴하지 않고 원하는 스타일을 지킨 게 정말 얼마나 대단한 일인지 모르겠어. 성인이 되고 대학가면서 하지도 않던 화장하고 꾸미고 그랬다가 이제는 다 버렸는데 그 과정이 쉽진 않았거든? 나도 언니처럼 살고 싶었나봐. 언제쯤 편한 머리에 편한 옷 입으면 남자라고 하지 않는 사회가 될까? 그래도 점점 인식이 변하는 것 같아. 탈코르셋이라는 거 어릴 적엔 상상도 못했던 생각인데 무의식적으로는 편안한 옷을 입고싶고 나를 검열하려는 시선들에서 벗어나고 싶었던 것 같아. 내 어린 시절부터 지금까지 항상 함께해줘서 고마워. 이름부터 보석인 언니가 항상 행복하기만 하다면 그걸로 충분할거야. 늘 건강하고 즐겁게 살자. 🥰

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Amber Liu. The first time I ever saw you, it was through my older sister who was, and still is, absolutely obsessed with FX. I have been a K-Pop fan for about a decade now, but at this time, at least 5 years ago, I wasn’t acquainted with many groups. I saw the absolute glow in my sister’s eyes as she showed me endless FX music videos and talked about each member with such love and inspiration woven into each of her words. Since then, I have been a huge supporter and fan of FX, and I have grown alongside you during your most difficult and triumphant times. I know that you have been through a lot, and even saying that doesn’t even come to close to what you must have been feeling for the past several years. I know you have been in the business and making music for a very long time now, and I know you have experienced extreme tragedy as well as glorifying victories. I have never seen someone respond to any obstacles in the mature and hopeful manner that you have. That, as I’ve gotten to know more about you over the years, might be what I appreciated the most about you. I am so aware why so many people, including my sister who introduced me to you, are so inspired by you and desperate to follow in your footsteps. Amidst all of the pain you have felt, sacrifice you have made, and challenges you have faced, you continue to make barrier-breaking music and share your voice with the world through that music. Your response to the problems in the world is so wholesome, genuine and confident; and you have taught many around the world how to effectively recover from any pain they may have felt. It can be understood that you have gone through what many have not, and yet you have not given up on living out your dreams and encouraging others to follow in your footsteps. What has always stood out to me is that you have always been confident, and done what has been best for you, rather than listen to others. You always came off as so comfortable in your own skin, and that makes you such an iconic performer and musician. Your powerful and bold rapping, combined with your soulful, smooth, and energetic voice makes you an incredibly compassionate performer who is so connected to her audience and music on stage. You are an unbelievably beautiful dancer and have such a demanding stage presence that has been such a privilege for me to watch over these years. I know that your fans love you in a way that’s stronger than anybody else ever could. You have given them a reason not to give up trying when the worst happens to them, and there is no higher form of inspiration than that. I am proud to be one of these fans, and I know my sister is as well. Similarly, your members love you and have such an unbreakable bond with you that I have seen firsthand without even knowing any of you personally. I know that you have all relied on each other in such a way that most people can’t say they know or understood, and I can’t even speak on how unique your relationship is with one another. I can’t even thank you enough for coming into my life and showing me confidence, strength, and reliance on my passion, friends, and family in the darkest times in my life. You are an inspiration like no other, and I know all of the fans, and even those outside of them can recognize as such a once-in-a-lifetime authentic musician. On behalf of your friends, fans, members, and most importantly, your loving and adoring family, I wish you the most blessed birthday ever Amber. I hope nothing but love surrounds you and those close to you always and forever. Please stay safe, and I pray that you continue to live your life in such bliss as you do now and have always tried to. I absolutely love you so, so much, and Happy Birthday! I hope you have as much fun as you possibly can!

author: @MiriaJiyuu
text:
To anyone who has gotten offended by people asking if Amber is a boy or a girl....

She can look like a boy or girl. I know who Amber is and I've still been fooled by her wearing a suit in a crowd for a second before I realize it's her. She has some feminine features and some masculine ones and overall someone who doesn't know her could easily think she's male or female, depending on where you look first. The astounding number of people who think she's a guy a first should tell you that maybe there's something about the way she carries herself can make her seem male. 

Don't get so offended by it, instead just inform them she's a girl. CURE their ignorance instead of making fun of them. There's never a need to be an asshole about something. Not everyone can easily tell she's a girl, not everyone has the same background knowledge you do.

If I saw just an image from this video with no sound and no idea what I was looking at (as in I know nothing about KPop), in particular the final image with her arm around Taeyeon would really do it,  I would totally think she's a guy. Hell I might even ask if her and Taeyeon were dating.

Anyway point is, be nice and don't take something so small so personally. It's really not as obvious as some of you think.

author: @AngelaRichardson_Locket_Shawol
text: It's all about the music. Kpop music. I'm a dedicated Shawol extremely addicted to all things SHINee lol, SHINee stole me away from EXO who first stole me away from Rain haha. Of course EXO and Rain make excellent music so I can't help but fangirl over em.' It's going on a year and a half of my SHINee indulgence so I'm always been introduced to other Kpop through them. Like Ga-in, VIXX, Infinite, 2NE1, Miss A, Spica, Ft. Island and many more...anyway, that's how I learned about F/X's Amber, my Ultimate Bias Key was on We Got Married Global 2 almost a year ago & ever since I've been curious about Amber singularly. plus Tasty and Gott7. Now that Amber has a solo project I thought I'd check her out. I wasn't even surprised that I loved her  song within seconds of hearing it. I mean it's fresh, upbeat, the type of song to elevate my mood. More please:) I also love rap in Kpop and Amber's flow just put her own my list of albums to buy this summer. I need more energetic songs like this. Now I'm really curious so it's finally time for me to check out F/X.

author: @tenkolee
text: So one day I was bored. I turned on our ps4 which is hooked up to our tv in the living room and was watching Amber's MV on it. My older brother who only knows about a few Kpop singers, especially Ailee and Lee Hyori, approached the tv and was like " who's that?" I told him "its Amber from F(x) who is the first member to go solo." I then proceed to ask, "so, do you think she is a girl or guy?" He looks at me and goes "well duh if anyone can tell it's a girl. What kind of guy would go by the name Amber. That's obviously a girl's name." I literally laughed at his response and said, "well most people think she's a guy because the way she is dressed." My brother then proceeds to say, "well those people who think like that are either dumb in nature because they can't comprehend that 'Amber' is a feminine name or either blind as fucking hell."(looks at TV) Woot way to tell me big bro. The only time I actually agreed with my older brother.

author: @tziporah9788
text:
The song is somewhat catchy and overall os good. Very sad to hear people can't respect Amber's choice of short hair and "boyish cloths" (cloths do not define someone's gender..?) as well as people using the wrong pronouns for Amber. I think that one of the only things that I find just ironically funny is that in this video, Amber incorporates the Whip Dance, and the Nae Nae, BOTH originating from African Americans late last year early this year(youtube it), and yet there are still many Koreans (not all of course) that are racist/prejudiced to black people or do not like black people despite their idols getting their dances and beats from them. There's a song where the artist goes "now watch me whip. Now watch me nae nae" and they do both dances in that order exactly like Amber's song.

Idk :// it just upsets me when people take from other cultures when people of their population don't even fully reconize me, my family, and my friends as a race as well as other cultures in general.

However the song is nice, and the dance is nice. If you like those two dances in particular for being "original", support the African American community and look at some African Americans dancing to it. :)

Not here to fight, but I AM here to spread word that this isn't something that Amber's dance choreographer invented him/herself. :]

To the people hating on Taeyeon for dating Baekhyun: If you were really a fan of Baekhyun and Taeyeon, you'd support them. text: I get why people said Taeyon not needed in this amber solo debut mv. Goddess llama, Hyeyeon, Miss A's Min and Jia, GOT7's Jackson, GOD's Joon , Ahn Young Mi, Busker Busker′s Brad, Rainbow′s Woori, Crayon Pop′s Ellin, NU′EST′s Aron, C-Clown′s Rome, and the beautiful Irene. author: @NowhereBeats
text:
Anyone else think the arrangement is what is stopping this from being a really great song?

1. The part at 0:56 which also appeared at 1:52 should only have appeared in once, having it twice killed the momentum.

2. The whole chorus.
---Tae's vocals (if 'ha-ha' counts as vocals) in the chorus should not have been there.
---The slow down in the instruments on the 4th bar totally ruins the feel too.
---That na-na-na-na part is unlistenable for me, the song would instantly be miles better without it.

3. That 'I want you too' was such a waste of time, a third verse by Amber would have been suitable.

4. It would have been nice to hear Amber rapping along side Taeyeon, rather just having ad-libbed 'uh huh'. 

5. Not an arrangement problem, but the bells in the instrumental ruin it.

6. Why hasn't SM given me a job yet.

author: @brambleheart1818
text:
I absolutely adore this song and love Amber to death, but Taeyeon's voice wasn't, in lack of better wording, strong enough for this song.
No hate on Taeyeon, I like her and all, it's just her voice wasn't compatible for a song like this and didn't stand out enough as it should've against the loud trumpets.
A good example would be at 2:38. Her voice sounded soft and kind of distorted the picture in my head of the song. However, her solo was good, though I would've like her vocalization part (3:03) to have ended on a higher note instead of letting it go lower by two notes or so. It would've given the next chorus a bit more pump and adrenaline. Not gonna lie, she blended nicely with the chorus and Amber.
I understand that SMent. was trying to play it smart as Amber isn't the most popular of f(x) in Korea and while I agree that Taeyeon brought a lot more views to this video than if Amber was alone, I would've just liked someone with a bolder voice singing.
Remember, this is just the personal preference of a thirteen year-old nobody.

text:
This was an extremely good marketing strategy from sm from the game:
1. It was able to motivate people to play the game again if they dropped it or to keep playing it for more of its benefits
2. It was able to attract views for a debuting solo artist (with a talent that should not be underrated) and
3. It was able to introduce this game to other people through the comments section on this video

This could be a good thing or a bad thing depending on how you see it.

author: @annlee1852
text:
Okay, so I've been watching this MV over and over again and I've finally got myself to comment~
This MV is awesome, well to me it is anyways! :) this MV is colorful, bright and really catchy and poppy, along with the simple dance movements. If I remember correctly when I first knew about Kpop, it was defined quite similarly to what this MV is like, Amber did put in her style and made it really fun. It was cool to see a huge variety of idol appearances in the MV, which you don't get to see often. 
Also, no hate on Taeyeon, she's a great singer with amazing vocals that went with the song. 'Shake That Brass' is one of my favorite songs to listen to cos it gives me such a happy vibe that I can't really explain. 
All in all, just enjoy the video and shake that brass!! ^^ <3

author: @ForgottenCharacter
text:
The song from the getgo I thought was awesome--the video took me a few views to become more okay with.

It's more the film and editing rather than the actual footage itself---it just seemed choppy or off beat at times, which made it difficult. Like lips not syncing by a lot for a second, or a dance looking very lax or uncoordinated. It was always very brief seconds of awkward that could've been overlooked and forgotten, except they added up with one another to cause disjunction for me as a viewer.

However, the footage subject did seem to replicate some of YG's past MVs, but not with the same kickass flare. Because of course SM doesn't want to actually be YG or produce the same images at all. So the resulting style wasn't badass like YG's attempted portrayals, but it also wasn't purely usual SM's fun/vibrant style---which came off here a bit goofy and undefined because of it.

The more I watched, the easier it became to ignore. Mostly because the song is FREAKING FANTASTIC, and also because I've adored Amber since LAchATA~

My second favourite song from her solo album is "I wanna" featuring Eric Nam, which is fantastic. And while Amber isn't a powerhouse singer, when she's not rapping she has such a beautiful sweet quality to her voice that's just wonderful.

I hope she comes out with more solo albums. This one's fantastic

author: @kraftcheeze7518
text:
As an African American. I have two opinions about this video. Number one, the video is HOT! The beat is nice, the style is fresh. Its a really nice song. HOWEVER, I wonder why African American style, culture, slang, and dance is so popular, but we have to deal with so much racism and stereotype. If I go to visit Korea as a Black man dressed Hip hop style, Im I going to be viewed as well as the way my culture is being mimicked and copied or am I going to be seen as some dangerous Black American...

Is Black culture mimicked because its is enjoyed and appreciated..
Do Korean People understand what Hip Hop and Black Culture is or is this all just entertainment...

The dance is Black American, The style is Black American, but can I get the same respect and esteem in Korea or in the Korean American community...

author: @verkyu
text:
Personally, I think Taeyeon has a wonderful voice, she can hit high notes and executes them perfectly. But I don't think she or anyone should be in Amber's song/mv. It's a SOLO debut, meaning one person. We've waiting long for Amber's debut, and we all know f(x) is treated poorly (they haven't had a world tour yet, and they don't have an official fan name). I'm pretty sure that Amber could possibly hit that high note and do the ad libs, she can sing as well as rap.

I don't think SM understand what 'solo' means. This has happened before with other artists. Jonghyun had someone featuring in his title song, so did Zhou Mi, Henry and maybe even Kyuhyun (if you count Irene's appearance, which added nothing to the music video).

Of course, if it was Amber's choice to have Taeyeon in the song/mv, then that's fine, but SM needs to have more faith that artists will do well without having someone more popular feature.

text: Everyone has opinions. Whether it be about the music itself, or the artist, or other things entirely. Comments on here do actually get read a lot of the time by the artists themselves so you might want to watch what you say or how you say things on here (if you at least have a bit of humanity or emotion or care how others interpret your comment). If you are to say something, at least sound somewhat professional  and respectful. Just know that just because you may not believe or agree what one some person may be saying, it doesn't mean that others or yourself need to reply and start an argument that gets you nowhere, rather just making people irritated or angry instead. (My opinion) Amber eonnie your rapping is creative and smooth (I love that you used your nickname Llama in your lyrics) and your voice is just angelic. Your entire mini album Beautiful is all around amazing and I am so happy that it is constantly on replay. author: @_kyramisu_
text: As someone who is in band and plays the french horn (what Jackson is attempting to play), this video pains me to watch. I get that them trying to play the instruments is a joke but it is still extremely cringe-worthy for someone WHO ACTUALLY PLAYS A BRASS INTRUMENT to see a couple musical artists incorrectly holding/trying to play legit musical instruments. There are a lot of other artists that have done this (Big Bang, Block B, Junhyung, etc) thinking that it makes them look 'cool' and 'sexy' when, in the eyes of people who actually know a great deal about music and musical instruments, they just look ignorant and ridiculous. No hate on Amber or any other idols though. I love her and this song. Especially the French horn synth in the first chorus! >u<

I understand you have your opinions and all, but no one asked for any haters on Taeyeon or on Amber for letting Taeyeon be featured. I don't see any real fans complaining about how many JYP artists that are cameoing in the MV, so don't complain about Taeyeon. author: @KissMissQUEenn
text: I'm a fan of both Girls' Generation and f(x), therefore I'm staying neutral and expressing my own views, without biasing or hating on anybody. First, this has disappointed me a bit. (Btw, another one one this album, "Beautiful" is real fabulous! i like it!) I think in terms of the rhythm, this is neither catchy nor hilarious, I expect more than that from Amber. Amber is a great singer (I do think she's even better than Krystal) and rapper (no offence she's really good and has her own style) yet she doesn't fully show it off here,especially singing, is it? And the song is quite dull, seriously. Second, Taeyeon is good, but I think her voice doesn't suit the song. Why didn't Amber choose Luna instead? I hope it isn't due to the popularity thing. Anyway, Taeyeon's voice is sentimental and perfect for ballad songs. So this one is truly not for her. I think voices like f(Luna)'s or GG's Tiffany's or RV's Wendy's, which are more powerful will do and meet the song's requirement.

author: @ItsMeRhaine
text:
Sometimes I really do hate the KPop fandom, everyone is so toxic, hateful, and immature at least 75% of the time, and I'm being really generous about that number. For once and for all can everyone just get along? Is that really too much to ask? It's like why do I even scroll down to the comments...
I'm not a huge fan of f(x), but I LOVE Amber and I know she worked her ass off for this song and mv as well as the entire album. This is AMBER'S MOMENT not Taeyeon... I am not here to hate on Taeyeon because I love her and SNSD (side note: I'm still butthurt over my girl Jessica gone...)
In all honestly I personally do not care about who got featured in whoever's video because at the end of the day what it really boils down to (imo) is if you simply just liked the song. Did you enjoy the song?
Ya'll being butthurt over Taeyeon and Wendy is overshadowing Amber's spotlight. Please do not steal her thunder, that she's worked so hard to get. Okay, I cannot stress enough that this is AMBER'S SOLO DEBUT and Taeyeon will get her chance in due time, which is apparently soon. Also for anyone wanting to know some trivia Amber was once way back in the day a huge fangirl for Taeyeon (and probably still is for all we know...?) and if Amber wanted Taeyeon to feature then cool beans.

Everyone just calm your tits because it's really all quite embarrassing, but hey what can I say that's the internet for ya... *major sigh* :/

PS: This song is great and I love it!

author: @nicizking
text:
Honestly, not hating Taeyeon, I mean I generally don't like her anyway, but besides my personal dislike towards her, I really didn't like her part in this song, it wasn't much of a part at all, a few high notes, and singing "shake that brass", and I don't know about anyone else, but did anyone else cringe and shiver when she sings that line at the end? The way she says "shake that brass", it just sounds wrong to me...

Well anyways, Amber did an awesome job, I really do like this song, I'm glad she had a chance to do her own solo thing. I'm actually kinda surprised most of the rap lyrics are in korean, I thought it would've been at least 50/50, english and korean. Good on her for rapping away in Korean very well!

I wish her nothing but success down the road as a solo artist and as our resident rapper. Congratulations, Amber!

author: @tyramcneil1345
text: Omg really, people? Taeyeon was obviously featured in order to increase views and interest. EVERYONE and they mama know that SNSD is THE most popular girl group (let's not get into debate over their quality, whether they deserve it, if ___ group has more fans -- let's face it and be honest, it's SNSD). Who, disclaimer -- I am relatively neutral towards (Here because Amber's cute yo). Being honest, if I were Amber, I would ask Taeyeon to feature too! It's a smart move -- business wise. And as much as K-pop fans hate to admit it, MUSIC IS A BUSINESS. PERFORMANCE, ENTERTAINING, FAME IS ALL A BUSINESS filled with business decisions. And as far as attention goes, Taeyeon was a great move! So many fans watch this JUST FOR TAEYEON. This is neither a good thing (because in that case how much substance will trickle down to sales? How many Taeyeon fans will feel compelled to then purchase this song or album? Because that will matter more than views) or bad (because it it still garnering attention for Amber even if not all or many Taeyeon fans spend money on this production). But this says nothing for the actual quality of the song/video (which is sadly going to promoted much more than Beautiful because of the attention Taeyeon (and the other stars) will bring. So I don't get why people are 1. Mad at Taeyeon??? (Like... why?) 2. Here just for Taeyeon and trying to pass it off like they love Amber and the song too?? Like then buy the album otherwise, you lyin' and SM don't really care about your half assed opinion. /endrant

author: @hokeypokeykid
text:
Okay, usually I don't leave comments, but I feel like this is absolutely necessary. I am disgusted with the comments I am seeing on this video.

This is Amber's debut song, and you people who claim to be her fans want to shit on one of her good friends in the comment section? Seriously? She put a lot of effort into this song, and into including her closest friends in the video. Do you think she would be happy to see things such as, "Fuck Taeyeon," and "Taeyeon is so fake?" This is a song that showcases Amber's skills, and by placing your attention on the fact that Taeyeon is in the video and how much she "sucks" and "needs to go die," you are really making yourself look like a fool, and devaluing the time and effort spent to make a music video that YOU the fan are supposed to like.

Even though I'm only a casual fan of both Amber and Taeyeon, I'm just really hurt for the both of them, knowing that there are people who will come on a music video just to spread their ridiculous negativity. They are human beings too, and just as you wouldn't want to hear people telling you to "fuck off and die," they don't want to hear it either.

Congrats to Amber and Taeyeon for all of their hard work on this song. It's really catchy and I hope that the rest of Amber's solo career won't be marred by the disgusting hate that is present in this comment section.

author: @LadySunghee
text:
One funny thing I noticed about this song is that it sounds like a typical KPOP song in reverse. I mean, in a typical KPOP song, vocalists will take up like 3 minutes and 30 seconds of a song while rappers need to squeeze in everything they (2-3 members) have to say in like 45 seconds. The rest of the song, if it's funky upbeat, they'll be shouting adlibs like "wooh" or "yeah", The reason why this is reverse is finally, there's a rap-song which features a vocalist and keeps the vocalist a feature. Because I have heard enough upbeat-funky-rap songs with half the main rapper and half the "featuring" artist.

I'm NOT saying that I didn't like the Taeyeon touch though.

Ok,that's one of the main reason why i was ranting...Just look at these comments..
"Came here only for Taeyeon" "This song sucks but my Taeyeon is in it!"
Ugh,why do i have to deal with it...
Dear Taeyeon fans,I'm glad you're here because of Taeyeon. But those comments,are they really necessary? This is Amber solo (If I wasnt clear enough,look at the title),so how about you write something like "Oh hey,I'm here for Taeyeon,but this song is really cool! I support Amber!" Also,didn't like the song? Good for you. MOVE ON.
I don't know what did you guys expect. A super deep and meaningful song? Showcase of her singing abilities? (Go listen to the mini-album if you want those.) This is a fun and catchy song,and I didn't expect anything else.
So please,if you have nothing else to do then to hate on Amber or Taeyeon,go try bunjee-jumping or something. I hope the rope breaks.

author: @ichigoiruka18
text:
I love Amber and I love this song! It's a lot of fun to listen to. (And I love that she put "llama" in it XD)
And I also believe that Taeyon's vocals were well mixed into the song and definitely added something. HOWEVER, that being said, I also feel that, by giving Taeyeon the ending note, it kind of upstages Amber a bit at the end as the final focus will be on Taeyeon instead of Amber.  But on the whole I enjoyed the interplay of rap and singing and liked that, instead of the usual mix of mostly singing and 1 rap bit, it was reversed so that it's mostly rapping with a singing bit (if that makes sense).
On the whole, I enjoy listening to this song and only hope that Amber has more vocal/singing lines in the future since she does have a nice singing voice :) Amber fighting!
Oh and if Eat Your Kimchi  can do their next Kpop Music Mondays about this video, that's be awesome! ^^

author: @junetan5047
text:
Okay can people stop hating on Taeyeon. Read this article: http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/02/amber-explains-how-she-got-taeyeon-to-feature-in-shake-that-brass 

Amber ASKED Taeyeon to be in this, so she must have thought that Taeyeon's vocals can complement this song well. Now whether Taeyeon's vocals actuall sound nice or not its for you guys to decide, but please stop blaming Taeyeon or GG for butting into things because they are not. 

As for view counts, I am a SONE and have to admit that if not for Taeyeon I would not have checked this out. Given Taeyeon and GG's popularity, I would say that their involvement would no doubt help Amber, but I know that Amber is also highly popular so she can also uphold popularity on her own account. 

In all, you guys can criticise this song/vocals all you like because you are entitled to your own opinions, but stop blaming innocent people before actually getting to know the truth and your own baseless prejudices.

I feel like it shows that she doesn't take herself too seriously, and she's willing to do fun little projects like this which will help her hoobaes.

text:
I honestly don’t understand how some people think Taeyeon “stole the spotlight” or whatever? Like, okay, I get it. You’re butthurt because she’s dating/dated Baekhyun, or maybe because she’s the leader of SNSD and was supposed to keep Jessica from leaving the group, etc, etc. But this is AMBER’S VIDEO. I mean, if you’re having trouble READING THE DESCRIPTION AND THE TITLE AND BY LOOKING AT HOW LITTLE THERE IS OF TAEYEON AND HOW AMBER’S IN THE VIDEO 99.5% OF THE TIME, then…. I think you need help or something? Maybe a tutor…? Because it’s not that hard to comprehend how Taeyeon’s just a featured artist.. (though Taeng did a great job at adlibbing and she looked amazing, but that’s not my point).

POINT IS, please stop all these rude comments directed to Taeyeon? It’s a really fun video and Amber's a good person, so we should all be here to support Amber, and not bring other artists down.

Thanks!

author: @adriana12995
text:
I love Taeyeon and I think she is super talented but I feel like her presence was unnecessary in here. I mean, in my opinion, i think Amber pretty much caught everyone's attention from the  beginning of the video without the help of anyone else. SM tends to do this when making a solo song for their artists. They always have to include someone more popular from the company to ensure it catches attention but in this case Amber did not need anyone else. Full rapping with no singing part would have been perfectly fine. 

On another note great song! I thought it would be another one of sm's meh songs but I actually really liked it, especially the cool dancing, which is something we don't really see from sm female artists.

author: @lovepuppy637
text: I am so proud of Amber finally getting her solo debut. She was the one who lead me to Fx and that made me a fan right from the start. Amber has always been my favorite k-pop artist because of how unique she is and how she is so cool and friendly. She is one of the funniest and nicest people I have ever seen. It disappointed me that she didn't sing much in Fx's songs but her rapping made up for it :) I think she deserved this, to get the spotlight and show off all her talents. I cherished every moment with seeing Amber and Fx on stage performing their hearts out. And it broke my heart when promotions for Red Light were stopped. Though this is one of the best things to happen, Amber getting her debut. No matter what happens I will always be a Fx fan and an Amber fan (llama). I hope everyone takes this to heart.

text: To be honest they could've taken this song on a whole other level. I love the fact that they added trumpets and so many cool raw instruments definitely one of the coolest solos. I felt like Taeyeon's note could've been longer. Her small high pitched notes in the end sorta drifted from the song.. it's like it shouldn't have been placed there. It reminded me of the notes in Twinkle. They were not structured to be placed their. She is an amazing vocalist. Maybe even one of the best in K-pop but SM needs to work on mixing the synths and rhythms with the vocals. I'm not saying their not good at it , but I think they need to work on it. It could totally make the music way more suitable for the ears. Amber did amazing but couldn't they add singing parts..? I think everyone (mostly) wanted it. (I mean I did) but anyways I really liked it otherwise. 황색 그런데 항상 랩과 훌륭한 일을 했어! #Amber #Fighting!

author: @extraleague01
text:
I love this song and the MV! It's pure fun and goodness! TBH, it's been quite sometime since I really liked a new Kpop song. I also like this probably cuz I like fast beat rap songs, as I find most slow beat rap songs quite boring. Love all the appearances by Amber's friends. There were pleasant surprises like Busker Busler's Brad, GOD's Joonhyung, comedienne Ahn Youngmi, Miss A's Min and Jia. This is really an Amber song that I wanted to listen to, spiced up by Taeyeon's beautiful voice towards the end. FYI, Amber asked Taeyeon to sing in her song.

BTW, I assume that 95% of people who don't likely Taeyeon's appearance here are either Taeyeon haters or SNSD haters, most likely NOT Amber fans, since most of these people don't even mention Amber (LOL) when talking about how Taeyeon appears a lot, which isn't true at all. Taeyeon's singing part only comes out towards the end and her total appearance is maximum 45 seconds out of the 3min38s length. These haters are so focused on Taeyeon that they completely forgot about Amber who appears on most of the MV, LMAO.

Anyways, I'm looking forward to live stages in music shows. Too bad Taeyeon won't be performing on the stage. Hopefully, she makes at least one appearance, maybe along with all those friends together!

author: @breadstal
text:
Not the biggest fan of the song; the beat is nice but the rest....not so much. The chorus and the rest of the song doesn't seem to connect very well. Taeyeon's "Uh Huh"and "Oh Yeahs" get really annoying after a while, it sort of reminds me of MissA's Hush when they say "Yeah" very often and it gets so repetitive.

I love how Amber had her friends take part in the video! Amber shows off how well her connections are. XD Taeyeon was highly unnecessary though; her part didn't do much for the song. And yes, I do understand that Amber asked her to participate in the video and song but that won't change how I feel about her part. I am excited to see how Wendy will sing alongside Amber for her debut stage!

Though this song was a let down for me personally, I can't wait to hear the rest of the album because Beautiful was just...beautiful. Still so proud of our llama!!

Y'know what? I'm not a Sone, but I actualy like Taeyeon in this. Her and Amber's vocal "tones" are very different, so she brings another sound into the song and it works. Yes, Amber could have done it all by herself, but with another singer featuring there's an extra element of variety that otherwise wouldn't be there. The only thing I'd change about this is give her more to do - that girl can really dance, and you've got her doing little more than sitting on a box fluttering her eyelashes during a song with a pretty cool routine? Come on.

author: @soomi_mp3
text: Please don't get me wrong. I love f(x) .. but I seriously thought Taeyeon did a better job than Amber did. I know you can't compare them, but its just my personal opinion. I'm not even a sone or a Taeyeon fan to be honest. The song throughout was rather flat and lots of repetitive 'shake that brass' parts. All together I felt like I was listening to 2 or 3 different songs at once, just mixed and blended here and there. There wasn't a moment when tension builded up where the song really grabbed my attention, because there was no actual climax in this. I'm just not a big fan of layed-back type of songs I guess. Please don't shoot me, it's just my personal opinion. Go ahead and like it if you want. I do support Amber. I love her.

author: @josefina121
text:
Ok but her album is so good?? Shake That Brass is a really happy, upbeat and colorful song that makes you wanna dance and jump around. Then there is Heights which gives me a night-like feeling, and her vocals are amazing. And I Just Wanna is simply perfect and one of my favorites bc i never thought  that she would release the english version of Goodbye Summer (even though featuring kyungsoo would have been like 10 times better because of his english accent lol, but still, I'm glad that she featured Eric, he definitely needs more recognition). And Beautiful is a beautiful (yeah, ironically), especially the lyrics at the rap part, it's that one song that cheers you up when you're feeling down. And finally, Love Run seems like that sweet romantic song (and the chorus has me feeling some type of way and I love it!).

For some reason I expected a lot from Amber and her album happens to be amazing, I think I have never liked all the songs of and sm album before like to keep listening to all of them for the rest of the day. Congrats Amber!

tldr: her album is amazing and you should all support her by buying it or watching the music videos!

author: @cheffaaay
text:
Just as I have feared.

Good MV. Love the cameos. Amber is a good rapper but she apparently is a way better singer but she gets essentially no singing lines in the song she's gonna promote for *her* debut. I'm callin' it now. I like Beautiful a heck lot more.

After listening to this song which line did you remember most? Without the help of the MV, I'm doubting it's catchy enough. I played the song in Superstar SMTOWN and they cut the game before the singing started. I feared it would be like this. I was hoping SM would prove me wrong. Oh how very disappointing.

Still, 화이팅! TEAM LLAMA ALL THE WAY!

(I am hoping the other tracks have lots of Amber singing. And I hope the rumored duet with Eric Nam is cute. And she's gonna sing.)

author: @Hyxnjxn
text: That was cute. Better than I expected. I thought Teayeon wasn't really gonna sing at all once I saw that I was getting towards the end of the video and then she did end up singing something and it fit the song very well. Her voice goes with amber's very well. And for people saying asking "why is there a need for Taeyeon" well let's see. She harmonises with Amber throughout the entire song from beginning to end. Then when Taeyeon actually sings her part. It's supposed to be the climax of the song. Now if you removed Taeyeon and just had Amber rapping through the entire song. Their would be no harmonies. There would be no climax to the song. You're practically removing a musical element that gives the song it's depth and makes it complete. Also if it was just Amber rapping the entire song you guys still would have found something to complain about. So Taeyeon fit the song perfectly. And since I mentioned harmonies those harmonies between Amber and Taeyeon while Amber was rapping. Flawless. People said Taeyeon would outshine Amber. False. Taeyeon didn't outshine Amber and believe it or not Amber didn't outshine Taeyeon. It was a perfect blend of Amber and Taeyeon.
